[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    276[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mStep 4: Generate the draft response.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Call the foundation model with the assembled prompt. Key parameters: use a low temperature (0.3-0.5) for consistency and predictability. Higher temperatures produce more creative and varied output, which is the opposite of what you want for healthcare communications. You want the same type of question to produce a similar style of response every time. Set a maximum token limit to prevent runaway generation. For routine messages, 200-300 tokens is plenty.[K
