[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    330[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mSkip this step, or get it wrong, and you'll have two classes of problem. First, stale features: a patient's engagement rate was computed last week and doesn't reflect a failed reminder that happened yesterday. The risk score is then predictably wrong. Second, feature drift between training and serving: the training data was produced with a slightly different feature computation than the serving pipeline uses. The model performs worse in production than it did in evaluation, and you won't know why until you trace through the features by hand.[K
