[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    788[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRecipe 3.1 (Duplicate Claim Detection):[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Shares the blocking-scoring-routing architecture, the feedback-loop pattern, and the baseline-for-thresholding approach. If you've already built 3.1, much of the operational infrastructure for this recipe is reusable.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    789[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRecipe 4.1 (Appointment Reminder Channel Optimization):[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The natural companion. This recipe identifies who to reach out to; 4.1 decides how to reach them. Best deployed together so the high-risk flags here drive the channel decisions there.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    790[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRecipe 4.5 (Adherence Intervention Targeting):[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Broader version of the same pattern applied to medication adherence rather than appointment-keeping. Shares feature-engineering approach, baseline computation, and intervention-effect measurement.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    791[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRecipe 6.3 (Patient Segmentation for Care Management):[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Uses similar features for a different purpose: cohort discovery rather than event prediction. A mature care management program typically runs both.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    792[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRecipe 7.4 (Readmission Risk Modeling):[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Structurally similar (prediction of a binary adverse event), but with much higher stakes and regulatory exposure. Treat this recipe as the warm-up; the patterns you develop here transfer directly but the governance overhead for readmission work is substantially heavier.[K
