[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    313[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mS2 (input-side Guardrails prompt-attack filters) is the fourth Chapter 2 finding in the same class (2.7 S2, 2.8 S2, 2.10 S2). The per-recipe fix is a single sentence in the Step 8 Guardrails comment block; the chapter-wide aggregate recommendation, which has now passed "recurring observation" threshold by a wide margin, is that Chapter 2's preface or a chapter-wide Guardrails-configuration appendix should consolidate the policy-level configuration checklist (input-side prompt-attack filters enabled, contextual grounding threshold specified, PII filters tuned for clinical content, denied-topics list scoped per recipe) once rather than repeating it in each recipe's Step 8 comment block. Each recipe can reference the appendix for the policy-level configuration and only call out recipe-specific configuration in its own Guardrails block.[K
